The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Tuesday, March 16, 2004 				 Disney hunts for film base
																								Mumbai, March 15 (PTI): Walt Disney Co is exploring India as a production base for its animation and feature films.																								Disney also plans to tap the countrys commercial abilities, including that in radio, animation, telecasting and content.																								India is a significant base for outsourcing of entertainment content and co-production, and we are on a fact-finding exercise in the country, Disney chief operating officer Andy Bird said here today.																								Bird, who had met information and broadcasting minister Ravi Shankar Prasad, said investing in radio, music and film industry would be the companys priority. The Disney official said the organisation intends to have a powerful presence in India. 																								Prasad said he had briefed Bird on the regulatory and cultural framework. He added that the government would discuss all possibilities, including tieups. 
